This and the fourteenth ode celebrate the victories in 15 amc of the young Neros, Drusus and Tiberius, stepsons of Augustus. ln the spring of that year Drusus, then but twenty-three years old, led his troops up the river Atagis (Adige) and defeated the Vindelician forces not far from Tridentum (Trent). He then pushed northward across the Brenner pass and defeated the Breuni and Genauni in the valley of the river Inn.
